al LLM Context | Python  •   Engineered an agentic RAG system that extends the effective memory of local language models from ~33  conversations (5k - token context window) to 300+ conversations   —   a 9× improvement   —   by dynamically indexing,  compressing, and retrieving conversation histor y as semantic chunks.  •   Implemented keyword - indexed per - session storage with relevance - ranked retrieval, ensuring the most  contextually important past exchanges are injected at inference time with zero context overflow   —   enabling truly  persistent long - term memory for local LLMs.  3F1 (Three Faction Intelligence)   —   Triadic AI Debate Engine | Live at 3f1.in  •   Engineered a Neural Debate Architecture with three autonomous LLM agents   —   Analyst, Critic, and Synthesizer  —   engaging in structured adversarial debate to produce bias - reduced, cross - validated conclusions.  •   Integrated RAG to ground agent responses in retrieved context, reducing hallucination rates; deployed as a full -  s",
